;; **
;;; However, because of tour consists of every city given, the tour `[1 2 3 4]` is same as `[2 3 4 1]`, `[3 4 1 2]`, etc. To remove the redundant tours, we restrict each tour to start from the same `origin` city, which default to the first element of `cities`.
;;; 
;;; This can be achieved by prepending the `origin` city to all of the permutations of the rest of the cities.
;; **

;; @@
 (defn all-tours [cities]
   (map (partial into [(first cities)])
        (combo/permutations (rest cities))))
